Hey! I was about to start working on this as it's been bothering me, and found your PR. Thanks so much for taking care of this üôá. I'd like to hear your thoughts `transformValue` specifically:

I'm using this utility to simplify APIs for our design system's end users, for example, instead of `justify-content`, our grid-rows have a `center` prop (`boolean | boolean[]`). Would it be better to make this entire interface Generic with smart defaults?

```ts
interface LowLevelStylefunctionArguments<N = string | number, Scale = Array<string | number>> {
  prop: string;
  cssProperty?: string;
  alias?: string;
  tranformValue: (n: N, scale: Scale) => any;
}
```

This would make the following typesafe:

```ts
// theme values:
const buttonSizes = {
  xs: '8px',
  sm: '16px',
};

const buttonSize = style<keyof buttonSizes, typeof buttonSizes>({
  prop: 'size',
  cssProperty: 'padding',
  transformValue: (n, scale) => scale[n]
});

const gridRowCenter = style<boolean>({
  prop: 'center',
  cssProperty: 'justify-content',
  transformValue: shouldCenter => shouldCenter ? 'center' : 'flex-start'
});
```

